The Tanzanian police have arrested 12 foreigners who were found living in Dar es Salaam Region without residence permits, local newspaper Daily News reported on Tuesday. These aliens were nabbed during a crackdown launched in collaboration with the Immigration Department, Regional Police Commander Alfred Tibaigana was quoted as saying on Monday. "The crackdown aims at netting all aliens who are residing in the country illegally." the regional police chief said. He said that these aliens were from Kenya, Malawi, Rwanda, Somalia, Ethiopia, Britain and Uganda and they were found staying in different guest-houses in the capital city. Tibaigana disclosed that the crackdown follows an alarming increase in robbery incidents in the city, often implicating foreigners. Enditem 